<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="70" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic"><persName type="from">Baron Moncheur</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Belgium</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-05"><hi rend="italic">May 5,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: In continuation of the
                            communication I had the honor to address to your excellency on March 26
                            last, respecting the proposed convention relative to collisions and
                            assistance at sea, I am instructed to inform you that Brazil, the
                            Dominican Republic, and Roumania have notified their adhesion to the
                            draft.</p>
                        <p>I gladly embrace this opportunity, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bn. Moncheur.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>